5 A BILL FOR AN ACT ENTITLED: “AN ACT PROVIDING AN APPROPRIATION TO REIMBURSE LAKE
6 COUNTY FOR CONSENTING TO ASSUME FELONY CRIMINAL JURISDICTION; PROVIDING FOR
7 PERMISSIBLE USES OF THE FUNDS, LEGISLATIVE INTENT, AND STATE RECOGNITION AND
8 OBLIGATIONS; AND PROVIDING AN EFFECTIVE DATE.”
9
10 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF MONTANA:
11
12 NEW SECTION. SECTION 1. FUNDING TO LAKE COUNTY -- PERMISSIBLE USES. (1) THE LEGISLATURE
13 DIRECTS THAT FUNDS BE APPROPRIATED FROM THE GENERAL FUND TO THE OFFICE OF BUDGET AND PROGRAM PLANNING
14 AS PROVIDED IN [SECTION 3] FOR THE PURPOSE OF MEETING FINANCIAL REQUIREMENTS AND FUNDING SHORTFALLS
15 RESULTING FROM LAKE COUNTY CONSENTING TO ASSIST THE STATE IN THE STATE'S CRIMINAL JURISDICTION AND
16 ENFORCEMENT OBLIGATIONS UNDER PUBLIC LAW 280, 83RD CONGRESS, 1ST SESSION, AND AS SPECIFIED IN 2-1-301.
17 (2) FUNDS APPROPRIATED WILL BE APPORTIONED AND DISTRIBUTED IN ACCORDANCE WITH [SECTION 3] TO
18 TRANSITION FELONY CRIMINAL JURISDICTION ON THE FLATHEAD INDIAN RESERVATION TO THE CONFEDERATED SALISH
19 AND KOOTENAI TRIBES AND TO PAY FOR EXPENDITURES INCURRED BY LAKE COUNTY IN MEETING THE STATE'S PUBLIC
20 LAW 280 OBLIGATIONS.
21 (3) ALL OF THE FUNDS APPROPRIATED UNDER [SECTION 3] ARE SUBJECT TO LEGISLATIVE AUDIT.
22
23 NEW SECTION. SECTION 2. STATE RECOGNITION AND OBLIGATIONS. (1) THE LEGISLATURE
24 ACKNOWLEDGES THAT LAKE COUNTY HAS WITHDRAWN FROM PUBLIC LAW 280 BUT WILL ASSIST THE STATE IN
25 FULFILLING ITS OBLIGATION BY AIDING IN THE TRANSITION OF FELONY JURISDICTION TO THE CONFEDERATED SALISH AND
26 KOOTENAI TRIBES UNTIL THE APPROPRIATION IN [SECTION 3] ENDS. IF THE TRANSITION IS NOT COMPLETE BY JUNE 30,
27 2027, AND A NEW APPROPRIATION IS OBTAINED FROM THE 70TH LEGISLATURE, LAKE COUNTY MAY PROVIDE FURTHER
28 ASSISTANCE IN PROPORTION TO THE FUNDING AUTHORIZED.
