1 (2) THE LEGISLATURE ACKNOWLEDGES THAT IF RETROCESSION BY THE STATE OR THE TRIBES IS NOT
2 COMPLETE BY JUNE 30, 2027, LAKE COUNTY'S WITHDRAWAL FROM PUBLIC LAW 280 REMAINS EFFECTIVE, THE COUNTY
3 INCURS NO OBLIGATION TO REENTER THE AGREEMENT, AND THE COUNTY MAY AT ITS OWN DISCRETION CONTINUE TO
4 ASSIST THE STATE AND THE CONFEDERATED SALISH AND KOOTENAI TRIBES AS REQUESTED.
5
6 NEW SECTION. Section 3. Appropriation. (1) The following money is appropriated from the general
7 fund to the department of justice to reimburse Lake County for consenting to assume felony criminal jurisdiction
8 over any member of a federally recognized tribe and over Indian territory of OFFICE OF BUDGET AND PROGRAM
9 PLANNING TO BE DISTRIBUTED IN EQUAL SHARES TO THE CONFEDERATED SALISH AND KOOTENAI TRIBES FOR THE
10 TRANSITION OF FELONY CRIMINAL JURISDICTION ON THE FLATHEAD INDIAN RESERVATION AND TO LAKE COUNTY FOR
11 EXPENDITURES RESULTING FROM THE ENFORCEMENT OF FELONY CRIMINAL JURISDICTION ON BEHALF OF MONTANA
12 WITHIN the Flathead Indian reservation:
13 Fiscal year beginning July 1, 2025 $2.5 million $2,333,333
14 Fiscal year beginning July 1, 2026 $2.5 million $2,333,333
15 (2) The legislature intends that the appropriation in this section is considered part of the ongoing
16 base for the next biennium and every biennium until the state retrocedes from Public Law 280.
17
18 NEW SECTION. SECTION 4. SEVERABILITY. IF A PART OF [THIS ACT] IS INVALID, ALL VALID PARTS THAT ARE
19 SEVERABLE FROM THE INVALID PART REMAIN IN EFFECT. IF A PART OF [THIS ACT] IS INVALID IN ONE OR MORE OF ITS
20 APPLICATIONS, THE PART REMAINS IN EFFECT IN ALL VALID APPLICATIONS THAT ARE SEVERABLE FROM THE INVALID
21 APPLICATIONS.
22
23 NEW SECTION. Section 5. Effective date. [This act] is effective July 1, 2025.
24 - END -
